Disease: Congenital lactic acidosis, saguenay-lac-saint-jean type
Congenital lactic acidosis, saguenay-lac-saint-jean type is caused by genetic mutations in the following known gene(s): LRPPRC. Learn more about these genes by searching them on the National Library of Medicine (NLM)[https://medlineplus.gov/genetics/gene/]. Given these known genetic mutation(s), you may want to ask your health care team if genetic testing is right for you. Genetic tests are laboratory tests that use samples of blood, saliva, or other tissues to help identify changes in genes, chromosomes, or proteins. Genetic testing can help confirm or rule out a suspected genetic disease or can provide other useful information to your health care team. Learn more about genetic testing from the National Human Genome Research Institute (NHGRI)[https://www.genome.gov/FAQ/Genetic-Testing].
